      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "SQA procedures documented; version control and regression testing suite in place for the CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022R2). Required level 2 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver is a commercially validated code with documented SQA procedures. Version control logs and regression test results were reviewed and found compliant with required level 2 criteria. No custom solver modifications were introduced for this study."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes standard benchmark verification cases (lid-driven cavity, pipe flow) at required accuracy. Required level 2 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 code verification was confirmed via vendor-supplied benchmark documentation covering laminar and turbulent internal flow cases relevant to the pump geometry. Results are within accepted tolerances for level 2 compliance."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study performed with at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI < 5% on primary QoI (NIH). Required level 2 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted using meshes of 4.2M, 8.7M, and 17.1M cells. Grid Convergence Index on normalized index of hemolysis was 2.8%, below the 5% threshold. Achieved level 3 exceeds the required level 2, providing additional confidence in spatial accuracy."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, pressure rise, fluid properties) documented and traceable. Required level 2 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "FDA GCBP experimental conditions are fully documented in the published benchmark dataset. Flow rates (2–7 L/min), pressure differentials (60–120 mmHg), and blood analog fluid properties (glycerol-water mixture) are specified with measurement uncertainties. Conditions are traceable to calibrated instrumentation records."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation metric V) computed between simulation outputs and experimental data. Required level 2 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Velocity field comparison against PIV data yielded mean absolute error of 4.1% across the measurement plane at the primary operating point. NIH prediction error versus in-vitro measurements was 6.3% averaged across six operating conditions. Both metrics satisfy level 2 acceptance thresholds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (NIH, shear stress distribution, velocity field) are directly linked to the clinical risk of hemolysis in CPB applications. Required level 2 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI, normalized index of hemolysis, is the standard metric for hemolysis risk quantification in rotary blood pumps and is directly relevant to the intended use of identifying worst-case operating conditions. Secondary QoIs (velocity field, wall shear stress) support mechanistic understanding of hemolysis generation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments cover the operating envelope relevant to CPB use (3–6 L/min, 60–120 mmHg). Required level 2 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities encompassed six operating points spanning the CPB-relevant flow and pressure range. The FDA GCBP geometry is a representative benchmark for centrifugal blood pump hemodynamics. Validation conditions are sufficiently representative of the intended clinical operating envelope to support level 2 relevance."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence monitoring sufficient at MRL 2 without full round-off and truncation error decomposition. Required level 1 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, full decomposition of numerical solver error into round-off and truncation components is not required. Residual convergence to below 1e-5 for all transport equations was confirmed for each simulation. This is acceptable at required level 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Analyst training and simulation setup review sufficient at MRL 2. Required level 1 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup was performed by a credentialed CFD analyst with documented training in cardiovascular device simulation. A peer review of boundary condition specifications and solver settings was conducted prior to production runs. Formal use-error analysis is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form selection (SST k-omega turbulence, power-law hemolysis model) documented with literature justification. Required level 1 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on published literature demonstrating its suitability for rotating machinery with adverse pressure gradients. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is the standard for NIH prediction in rotary pumps. Model form justification is documented and appropriate for level 1 at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Nominal model inputs (fluid properties, rotational speed, boundary conditions) documented and traceable to experimental specifications. Required level 1 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs are traceable to the published FDA GCBP benchmark specifications and calibration records. Fluid viscosity and density were set per the documented glycerol-water mixture properties. Rotational speed and flow boundary conditions are consistent with experimental setup. Uncertainty propagation analysis is not required at level 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Single representative pump geometry used; sample variability analysis not required at MRL 2. Required level 1 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The FDA GCBP is a single canonical geometry used as a regulatory benchmark. Geometric variability across manufacturing samples is not within scope for this credibility assessment at MRL 2. The use of a single representative geometry is acceptable at required level 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters match experimental conditions within documented tolerances. Required level 1 for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Simulation boundary conditions were set to match experimental values within reported measurement tolerances (flow rate ±0.05 L/min, pressure ±2 mmHg). Full parameter equivalency mapping is not required at level 1 for MRL 2. The correspondence between simulation and experimental inputs is considered adequate for the intended screening application."
    }
